etymology.description: 𤣩 is a variant form of 玉(玉) (yù, "jade") which depicts a cong (琮), a ritual jade totem -> distinguished from 王(王) (wáng, "king") by adding a dot
etymology.interpretation: The character 𤣩 represents a variant of 玉(玉) (yù, "jade"), highlighting its historical use as a symbol of jade artifacts. By adding a dot to the original pictogram, it distinguishes itself from 王(王) (wáng, "king"), emphasizing its unique identity as jade.
